VALUES
('anchovy',FALSE,'https://acnhcdn.com/latest/MenuIcon/Fish81.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/BookFishIcon/FishAntyobiCropped.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/FtrIcon/FtrFishAntyobi.png',200,'Sea','Small','Very Easy','Very Wide',0,'2–5','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','04:00 – 21:00','1x1','No','There are more than 140 species of anchovy, but they do all have some things in common. They are small and feed by simply swimming with their mouths open to filter food particles from the sea. (In my sleepier moments, I sometimes wish_I could do that...)','I caught an anchovy! Stay away from my pizza!',71,'Pet','Blue','Red','No lighting','LzuWkSQP55uEpRCP5',56,'common',300),
('angelfish',FALSE,'https://acnhcdn.com/latest/MenuIcon/Fish30.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/BookFishIcon/FishAngelfishCropped.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/FtrIcon/FtrFishAngelfish.png',3000,'River','Small','Easy','Medium',20,'2–5','NA','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','1x1','Yes','The angelfish_is truly a beautiful creature. Just look at the elegance of those fins! Despite the name, however, these lovelies are known to be rather aggressive. They''ve no qualms about relentlessly pursuing fish_much smaller than themselves! Why, they even attack their own kin! It seems no fish_is safe around these "angelic" bullies. It makes one wonder who comes up with these names. Appearances— and names— can be deceiving.','I caught an angelfish! That other fish_told me to do it!',71,'Pet','Yellow','Black','Fluorescent','XTCFCk2SiuY5YXLZ7',36,'uncommon',4500),
('arapaima',FALSE,'https://acnhcdn.com/latest/MenuIcon/Fish36.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/BookFishIcon/FishPirarukuCropped.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/FtrIcon/FtrFishPiraruku.png',10000,'River','XX-Large','Very Hard','Narrow',50,'1','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','3x2','No','The stately arapaima is quite large. Indeed, it is among the largest freshwater fish_there are. Furthermore, these fascinating fish_make quite the family unit. That is to say, male arapaimas protect their young by holding them gently in their mouths. Meanwhile, female arapaimas swim circles around these full-mouthed fathers fending off predators. It simply goes to show that cold-blooded creatures can be heartwarming too.','I caught an arapaima! How did it get here? Arapaiknow!',71,'Pet','Black','Blue','No lighting','mZy4BES54bqwi97br',44,'rare',15000),
('arowana',FALSE,'https://acnhcdn.com/latest/MenuIcon/Fish33.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/BookFishIcon/FishArowanaCropped.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/FtrIcon/FtrFishArowana.png',10000,'River','Large','Very Hard','Medium',50,'1–2','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','16:00 – 09:00','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','16:00 – 09:00','2x1','Yes','It would seem your angling expertise knows no bounds! This beauteous arowana fetches a pretty Bell, though I''d venture to say that its true price is beyond measure. The arowana is an excellent jumper. Some have been seen  leaping six feet out of the water, eh wot! Alas, it has also been on the endangered-species list for some time. It''s up to us to do all we can to help preserve such magnificent creatures for the years to come.','I caught an arowana! I''d make a joke, but I don''t ''wana.',71,'Pet','Yellow','Black','Fluorescent','F68AvCaqddBJL7ZSN',41,'rare',15000),
('barred knifejaw',FALSE,'https://acnhcdn.com/latest/MenuIcon/Fish47.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/BookFishIcon/FishIshidaiCropped.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/FtrIcon/FtrFishIshidai.png',5000,'Sea','Medium','Hard','Medium',20,'3–5','NA','NA','All day','All day','All day','All day','All day','All day','All day','All day','All day','NA','All day','All day','All day','All day','All day','NA','NA','NA','All day','All day','All day','All day','1x1','Yes','Wonderful! I would love nothing more! The barred knifejaw, also called the striped beakfish, is a lovely fish_with a distinctive striped pattern. It is reportedly also a very curious fish_in that it has been known to approach swimmers to "greet" them. They also tend to be good at avoiding fishing hooks, so well done on outwitting this one!','I caught a barred knifejaw! They must have a hard time eating!',71,'Pet','White','Black','Fluorescent','X3R9SFSAaDzBF4fE3',58,'uncommon',7500),
('barreleye',FALSE,'https://acnhcdn.com/latest/MenuIcon/Fish84.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/BookFishIcon/FishDemenigisuCropped.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/FtrIcon/FtrFishDemenigisu.png',15000,'Sea','Small','Very Hard','Very Narrow',100,'1','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','21:00 – 04:00','1x1','No','The barreleye is a deep-sea fish_with protuberant eyes and a clear head, so some of its organs are... visible. At first blush, a transparent head seems absurd, but there is a reason: so it can see things directly above! But I must confess - the more I learn about deep-sea fish, the happier I am to live on dry land, wot.','I caught a barreleye! Like eyeing fish_in a barrel!',71,'Pet','Black','Black','Fluorescent','BpqTa4zmTjv3Nm4wE',79,'ultra rare',22500),
('betta',FALSE,'https://acnhcdn.com/latest/MenuIcon/Fish77.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/BookFishIcon/FishBetaCropped.png','https://acnhcdn.com/latest/FtrIcon/FtrFishBeta.png',2500,'River','Small','Hard','Narrow',20,'1–4','NA','NA','NA','NA','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','NA','NA','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','NA','09:00 – 16:00','09:00 – 16:00','1x1','No','The betta has long fins and beautiful coloring. It is a tropical fish_popular in decorative aquariums. They''re very territorial and will fight to complete exhaustion, so aquarists must keep them carefully. Rarely do such beauty and violence commingle outside the rowdiest of sunset-viewing parties.','I caught a betta! I betta not drop it!',71,'Pet','Aqua','Black','Fluorescent','7QcQXzwZoNGiNA94k',37,'uncommon',3750),
